<p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
<p><strong>(a)</strong> With $y$-axis: $f(0)=0$, point $(0,0)$. With $x$-axis: $x^3-3x^2+2x=0 \Rightarrow x(x^2-3x+2)=0 \Rightarrow x(x-1)(x-2)=0$. Points: $(0,0)$, $(1,0)$, $(2,0)$.</p>
<p><strong>(b)</strong> We study the sign of $f(x)=x(x-1)(x-2)$:</p>
