<li>The function $f(x) = x^2 - 2x + 2$ intersects the $x$-axis at:</li>
<li>a) Two distinct real points</li>
<li>b) A single point (tangent)</li>
<li>c) No real point</li>
<li>
<p>d) Infinitely many points</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Correct answer: c)</strong> Discriminant: $\Delta = 4 - 8 = -4 &lt; 0$. No real roots; the function does not cross the $x$-axis.</p>
</blockquote>
